  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Pruning reduces storage footprint while accelerating inference speed by approximately 20% and 40% when 8 and 16 layers are pruned, respectively, compared to the unpruned baseline, after full-parameter fine-tuning of both models on the English-to-German in-domain data.",
    "In contrast, 4-bit quantization as implemented in QLoRA reduces storage at the cost of inference speed.",
    "Given that the shared task prioritized minimizing storage requirements, we applied QLoRA to the pruned model in the final fine-tuning stage.",
    "For deployment scenarios where inference speed is critical, however, the pruned model can be fine-tuned with standard LoRA instead of QLoRA to avoid quantization overhead.",
    "It is common to fine-tune pruned models after pruning (Kim et al., 2023)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "It is common to fine-tune pruned models after pruning (Kim et al., 2023)."
  ]
}